# MCP for architecture

When designing, reviewing, or debugging **agentic / LLM systems**, use connected MCP tools before improvising from memory.

## Default server: agent-patterns

Endpoint: `https://mcp.agentpatternscatalog.org/mcp` (see `.cursor/mcp.json`)

| Situation | Call |
|-----------|------|
| New agent feature | `recommend_recipe` → expand composed patterns |
| Architecture review | Match design to catalog patterns; check anti-patterns |
| Runtime symptom (loops, tool hallucination, context blow-up) | `pattern_for_symptom` |
| Compare two approaches | `find_pattern` + related edges / trade-offs |
| Terminology / ADRs | `glossary_term`; cite **pattern ids** |

## Workflow

1. Check MCP is available (Settings → Tools & MCP)
2. Query catalog **before** finalizing architecture
3. Combine MCP results with skills: `agentic-system-design`, `system-design-tradeoffs`
4. Document chosen **catalog pattern ids** in plan or ADR when applicable

## If MCP unavailable

Fall back to `agentic-system-design` skill and [docs/MCP_SETUP.md](../../docs/MCP_SETUP.md). Note in response that live catalog was not queried.

## Other MCP servers

Optional: Context7 (library docs), GitHub (repo data) — see [docs/mcp-catalog.json](../../docs/mcp-catalog.json). Use only when task requires live external data.

Do not call MCP for routine CRUD coding with no agentic design component. Minimal-code discipline is enforced by `ponytail.mdc` + the `ponytail` skill — not by MCP.
